-- Brigham Young, Northern Illinois, Troy State Win as Football Bowls Begin
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2010-12-19T05:45:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/brigham-young-northern-illinois-troy-state-win-as-football-bowls-begin.html
Brigham Young University, Northern
Illinois University and Troy State University were winners as
the college football bowl season opened.  Jake Heaps threw four touchdown passes yesterday, including
scoring strikes of 31, 29 and three yards to Cody Hoffman, to
lead BYU to a 52-24 win against the University of Texas-El Paso
in the New Mexico Bowl in Albuquerque.  At the Humanitarian Bowl in Boise, Idaho, quarterback
Chandler Harnish ran for two touchdowns and threw for a third as
NIU defeated Fresno State University 40-17. Harnish threw for
300 yards and had 10 carries for 72 yards.  Troy defeated Ohio University 48-21 in the New Orleans Bowl.
Corey Robinson threw four touchdown passes and hit for 387 yards
for Troy, which led 38-7 at halftime. Boo Jackson had three
scoring tosses for Ohio.  To contact the reporter on this story:
